Money management is a skill that everyone should practice.  Financial illiteracy comes from a lack of awareness whereas  Financial immaturity comes from a lack of responsibility. Living on my own and owning multiple businesses at a young age matured me financially. I dictate what my money does for me, and I like to spend majority of my money on assets that produce more money. 

If you’re having trouble deciding what to do with your money, here are a few suggestions:
1. Buy and keep your money tied up in stocks.
2. Start a business. Buy and sell things for example. 
3. Move out and start paying bills. 
4. Buy real estate.
5. Lend it out to people who need it, and charge interest on the loan.
6. Pay off your debts.

Hope this helps🙇🏽‍♂️

Your team is one of the most important divisions in your company; they can make or break your business. By treating them properly, you’ll have less turnover and more efficient results. One quick way to ruin that relationship is to play with their money. 
.
#business #businessadvice #entrepreneur

An insecure person will project their insecurities on you. Viewing your team like family instead of a replaceable employee will raise the level of respect from both parties. True power is being able to handle it without it getting to your head. With great power comes great responsibility🙏🏽
.
#business #businessadvice #entrepreneur

A leader will show you instead of telling you. Displaying your competence to complete tasks you request from your staff will increase their productivity and morale. Being hands-on in your company by completing the tasks you require will also give you a better understanding of what your team has to go through, and if you’re an understanding person, you’d be able to make changes in how to complete those tasks, which will increase efficiencies within the work force.
.
